article.headline: Jacksonville St. 42, Austin Peay 9
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Quarterback Cedric Johnson rushed for 94 yards and scored four touchdowns Thursday night to help Jacksonville State beat Austin Peay 42-9. Johnson, who also threw for 139 yards, became the first player in Jacksonville State (4-3, 3-1 Ohio Valley conference) history to run for that many touchdowns. His longest of the four TDs was a 69-yard run with 7 minutes left in the second quarter. Austin Peay (4-3, 2-2) never really threatened. The Governors' only scores came in the first quarter on a 30-yard field goal by Isaac Ziolkowski and a 6-yard run by Chris Fletcher.
